
Permacoin and Zerocash

Last night, I attended a presentation on Permacoin by Andrew Miller and Zerocash by Eran Tromer. Both were thoughtful presentations that sought to push forward the field of research around novel applications for Satoshi Nakamoto's blockchain. Below is my summary of each presentation.

Andrew & his collaborators' research is based on the premise is that to utilize the computing power of Bitcoin to also build a massive distributed database of the world's information. 

